Flatcar Container Linux is an open-source, lightweight operating system specifically designed for running containers. It is a fork of CoreOS Container Linux and provides an immutable, minimal, and secure environment optimized for containerized applications. Key features include automatic updates, support for major container runtimes like Docker and Kubernetes, and easy integration into container orchestration systems. It is commonly used in cloud and edge computing environments where lightweight and secure operating systems are essential for running large-scale container deployments.
